before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"6b6hp","text":"Electroporation should occur at least 4 days prior to the intended Spizellomyces transformation time to ensure that active, single colonies are available to be selected and transferred to liquid culture the night before transformation day (see Protocol \"Growing liquid cultures of Agrobacterium prior to transformation day\").","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
description: {"blocks":[{"key":"f5mf6","text":"Electroporation is a widespread method of transforming competent Agrobacterium tumefaciens (Agro) cells with a plasmid containing a T-DNA of interest. The resulting Agro can be used to transform various plants and fungi, resulting in transformed cell lines. This protocol outlines the standard electroporation protocol we use to transform Agro in preparation for Agrobacterium-mediated transformation of the chytrid fungus Spizellomyces punctatus.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":65,"length":25},{"style":"italic","offset":92,"length":4},{"style":"italic","offset":339,"length":4},{"style":"italic","offset":363,"length":13},{"style":"italic","offset":423,"length":23}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"5pm3u","text":"Any binary plasmid that works in Agrobacterium tumefaciens strain EHA105 (GoldBio #CC-225-5x50) can be used for this procedure. We have had success using plasmids derived from pPZP201-BK (PMID: 7919218). It is imperative that all steps be carried out at 4℃ up until electroporation. Ensure proper sterile technique throughout this protocol; perform all steps except centrifugation and electroporation charge delivery in a laminar flow hood or in the sterile area around an open flame.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
